table_context:
It is one of a few categories which are open to both classical and non-classical recordings, new or re-issued. The Grammy Award for Best Immersive Audio Album (until 2018: Best Surround Sound Album) was first awarded in 2005, as the first category in a new "Surround Sound" field. On 24 November 2020 during the announcement of the nominations for the 63rd Grammy Awards, to be presented on 31 January 2021, the Recording Academy said there will be no winner or nominees in this category.
